{"type":"message","id":"10baae70","parentId":"7f2b0fe8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:09:28.158Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the most recent pulse log while the script is still running.","thinkingSignature":"2e595bf70fe9a0759849c9db66f562a871ba4ce789266c970a1973ad82aa7146"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y15xrksukwic_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 090816.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y15xrksukwic_2","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"quiet-claw","timeout":55000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":402,"output":111,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12650,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774357764701}}
{"type":"message","id":"0c19ccb9","parentId":"10baae70","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:09:28.168Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_y15xrksukwic_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 090816\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: tic_experiment.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and what action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n2. There's a pending TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n3. The next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that causal structure IS invariant structure. The next experiment is to test this on the last 20 pulse logs.\r\n\r\nLooking at the recent pulse file: `pulse_2026-03-24 090408.md`\r\n\r\nWhat concrete action can I take to advance the TIC experiment?\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Start implementing the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and their structure, then create an initial TIC experiment script or specification.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the pending action is to \"Implement TIC classifier on logs/pulse_*.md files\". This is a concrete next step.\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC experiment specification or initial implementation. I should look at what's in the logs directory first to understand the pulse log structure.\r\n\r\nSince this is a stateless discontinuous agent and I need to advance the goals, let me:\r\n1. Create a TIC experiment specification\r\n2. Or create an initial TIC classifier script\r\n\r\nGiven the \"prefer file edits\" instruction, let me create:\r\n1. A specification for the TIC experiment in research/\r\n2. An initial Python script for the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nActually, let me think about what would be most impactful. The goal is to:\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nI should create:\r\n1. `experiments/TIC/experiment_spec.md` - defining the experiment\r\n2. `experiments/TIC/classifier.py` - the initial TIC implementation\r\n\r\n\r\n3. `experiments/TIC/classifier.py` - the initial TIC implementation\r\n\r\nThe most direct path forward is to build the classifier script. I'll focus on creating a Python implementation that can process the pulse logs, identify invariant patterns, and begin testing the core hypothesis about causal structure and invariance.\r\n\r\nThe pulse logs contain critical metadata that can help establish baseline invariants like project context and goals. These structural elements remain consistent across sessions and can serve as anchors for detecting meaningful variations.\r\n\r\nMy immediate focus is implementing a systematic approach to analyze these logs, extract invariant patterns, and begin validating the core theory about causal relationships and structural consistency.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to examine the actual pulse log structure before implementing the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine the existing pulse logs to understand their structure, then create the TIC experiment directory and initial classifier implementation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure IS invariant structure. A compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- Invariant/variant classification accuracy: >70%\r\n- Next-pulse prediction accuracy: >60%\r\n\r\n## Methodology\r\n\r\n### Phase 1: Invariant Detection\r\n1. Extract structural elements from pulse logs (goals, actions, mutations)\r\n2. Classify elements as INVARIANT (stable across sessions) or VARIANT (changing)\r\n3. Measure classification accuracy against manual labels\r\n\r\n### Phase 2: Next-Pulse Prediction\r\n1. Given invariants from pulse N, predict pulse N+1 content\r\n2. Use invariant subset as compression of previous context\r\n3. Evaluate prediction quality\r\n\r\n### Phase 3: Compression Ratio\r\n- Compare original pulse size vs summarized (invariant-only) size\r\n- Target: >50% compression while preserving predictive power\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nIf hypothesis holds:\r\n- High invariant detection accuracy confirms causal structure detection\r\n- Good prediction accuracy proves invariants encode causal relationships\r\n- Validates Phase 1/Phase 2 unification\r\n\r\n## Status\r\n- [ ] Collect pulse logs (target: last 20)\r\n- [ ] Define invariant features\r\n- [ ] Implement classifier\r\n- [ ] Run experiment\r\n- [ ] Measure results against success criteria\r\nfile: experiments/TIC/experiment_spec.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: \"\"\"\r\nTIC Classifier: Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n\r\nDetects invariant vs variant elements in pulse logs.\r\nHypothesis: Invariants = causal structure\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nTIC_DIR = Path(\"experiments/TIC\")\r\n\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_features(pulse_path: Path) -> Dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structural features from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Section patterns\r\n    obs_match = re.search(r'### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    action_match = re.search(r'### ACTION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    mutation_match = re.search(r'### MUTATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    \r\n    features = {\r\n        'path': str(pulse_path),\r\n        'timestamp': pulse_path.stem.replace('pulse_', ''),\r\n        'observation': obs_match.group(1).strip() if obs_match else '',\r\n        'action': action_match.group(1).strip() if action_match else '',\r\n        'has_mutation': 'file:' in (mutation_match.group(1) if mutation_match else ''),\r\n        'mutation_file': None\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract mutation file target\r\n    if\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:08:54\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774357768166}}
